The perl interpreter is case sensitive. This means that identifier names containing lowercase letters will be treated as being different and separate from those containing uppercase letters:

 # These variables are all different
 $dog='Benjamin';
 $Dog='Samba';
 $DOG='Bernie';
 print "The dogs are named $dog, $Dog, and $DOG \n"

== Converting Strings ==

The perl interpreter provides the following functions for converting strings to uppercase or to lowercase:
uc 	Converts a string to upper case
lc 	Converts a string to lower case
ucfirst 	Converts the first letter of a string to upper case
lcfirst 	Converts the first letter of a string to lower case

