==Log== If there is a power of ten, 10<sup>b</sup> = a, then : log<sub>10</sub> a = b which is equivalent to log a = b
==Rules== # <math>log a + log b = log ab</math> # <math>log a - log b = log \frac{a}{b}</math>
{{BookCat}}

==Natural Log== If there is a power of two, 2<sup>b</sup> = a, then : log<sub>2</sub> a = b which is equivalent to Ln a = b
==Rules== # <math>Ln a + Ln b = Log ab</math> # <math>Ln a - Ln b = Log \frac{a}{b}</math>
{{BookCat}}

